role-description:
THE ROLE
You'll do analysis and tests to influence priorities, inform product development efforts, optimize existing website sections and measure the impact of the work done by the Product, Design and Engineering teams.
You will be responsible for creating and maintaining ongoing reporting/dashboards, running A/B and multivariate tests, performing ad-hoc analyses and creating tagging requirements for new features/pages

WHAT YOU'LL DO
Perform ad-hoc analysis and provide thought leadership in hypothesis development efforts;
Add value to requests from business leaders and build reporting logic that will produce analytical measures to tell the story of what is happening in the business. This requires a strong understanding of business processes and data flows;
Create and support customer analytics models to understand customer online behavior;
Create automated dashboards to measure KPIs and performs data validation;
Build great relationships with your business stakeholders and other analytics teams - influencing business KPIs, roadmaps and prioritisation
Identify and champion improvements in our capability, such as data developments, best practices, and L&D
Work in an agile fashion, and deliver on time and accurately

WHO YOU ARE
A professional with a minimum of 1 years of experience with data analytics, with e-commerce orientation (mandatory);
A graduate of a Bachelor of Science program or a higher level post-secondary educational program in Computer Science, Math, Engineering, Operation Research, or quantitative disciplines (desired);
Very skilled in Excel and SQL skills;
An excellent communicator with presentation skills, both verbal and written;
Very skilled in English, both written and spoken;
An excellent strategic thinker and with analytical skills;
Experienced in leveraging data and analytics to solve real-world problems and create new solutions;
An individual that can change directions quickly to respond to new information and changing circumstances;
Experienced with BI and data visualization tools (e.g., Looker, Tableau, etc.) is preferred;

Mission
Analyse data in order to influence priorities and inform the sales team about customer behaviour. Proactively offer project expertise and support on the data side for the efforts the team will pursue. Interact appropriately with external and internal stakeholders: Investigate, thoroughly, validate, findings adequately, provide information, data, proposed solutions, timeframes and confirmations.


Roles and Responsibilities
Work extensively on data mining and data analytics within Linde Plc's infrastructure, as well as develop data visualization infrastructure;
Data retrieval and management, data analysis for trends and use of data to influence decision making and help defining new business opportunities and trends within the company.;
Involved in technology development from concept initiation through commercialization and work closely with global business organizations;
Participate in the technical development and lead project execution involving multi-disciplinary teams;
Stay abreast of new technology developments in field of expertise and actively contribute ideas for new programs;
Support new data science development while maintaining and improving existing applications.


Competencies Required 
Degree in Computer Science, Statistics or related area;
2+ years of relevant industry experience;
Knowledge of SQL, Kubernetes, Docker and Kafka;
Knowledge Python, Java and R (a plus);
Data management and data integrity concepts;
Familiarity with data presentation tools, preferably Tableau;
Fluency in English (C1);
Proactive and eager to be on a multicultural environment.

