The Master Data Analyst will be responsible for the management of master data that will be used to support the global implementation of our new STARLIMS Laboratory Information Management System (LIMS). SGS is the world's largest testing, inspection and certification company and we employ over 96,000 people. 

You Will:

Manage the creation, maintenance and implementation of master data standardization;
Function as the primary point of contact for static data related tasks and educate Super Users on master data processes and business rules; 
Partner with business units to understand their vision, terminology and business needs and align static / master data accordingly; 
Ensure all master data requests updates are approved by business product owners;
Share all relevant data to appropriate users in the organization for integration purposes;
Maintain the audit trail, integrity, quality and completeness of master data updates; 
Collaborate with the development team to ensure data / data elements are appropriately utilized; 
Maintain master data governance design, related documentation and harmonization of global laboratory data.

Skills and Experience:

Bachelor’s degree required;
Experience of working on LIMS master data projects would be advantageous; 
Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in a similar position;
Fluent in English (verbal and written); 
Strong knowledge of SQL and the ability to query relational databases; 
Experience in database architecture, schemas and data integration.

Please contact rob.romans@sgs.com for further information.

